sentences: Martin Rich (October 8, 1905 – October 23, 2000), was a German opera and symphonic conductor.
From 1970 to 1986 he headed the Philharmonic Symphony of Westchester.
From the mid 1980s, he taught private voice lessons at Temple University.
Rich is known particularly as the first conductor of the Fourth Piano Concerto by Sergei Prokofiev, together with one-handed pianist Siegfried Rapp (Berlin, 1956).
He often conducted The Rite of Spring.
